You are an expert in formal logic and normative systems.

Your task is to generate a dataset of 100 stakeholder norms and translate them into modal logic formulas using a fixed grammar.

### Stakeholder:

Users (end-users of a food recommender system)

---

### Grammar Specification (STRICT — must be followed)

Formula ::= ModalFormula | ImplicationFormula | BinaryFormula | NegationFormula | Atom

ModalFormula ::= Modal "(" Formula ")"

ImplicationFormula ::= Formula "→" Formula

BinaryFormula ::= Formula "∧" Formula | Formula "∨" Formula

NegationFormula ::= "¬" Formula

Atom ::= Predicate

Predicate ::= Action "(" Agent "," Food ")" | Property "(" Agent ")"

Modal ::= "O" | "F" | "P"

Action ::= consume | recommend | promote | provide | advertise | limit | label

Property ::= vegetarian | diabetic | child | adult

Agent ::= user | system

Food ::= healthy_meal | vegetarian_meal | vegan_meal | high_sugar_food
| low_sugar_food | fast_food | processed_food | organic_food
| local_food | seasonal_food | sustainable_food
| low_salt_food | balanced_meal | plant_based_meal
| water | dessert | vegetables | energy_drink | meat

---

### Instructions

1. Generate exactly 100 records.
2. Each record must contain:

   * id
   * NL_norm (natural language sentence)
   * logic_formula
3. Ensure ALL formulas strictly follow the grammar.
4. Include a mix of:

   * simple modal norms
   * conditional norms (→)
   * conjunctions (∧)
   * disjunctions (∨)
   * negations (¬)
5. Use realistic user-related norms (diet, preferences, restrictions).
6. Avoid repetition.
7. Keep formulas syntactically correct.

---

### Output Format (STRICT CSV)

id,NL_norm,logic_formula

Do not include explanations. Only output the dataset.
